# This is the commands to add a HDD into the server for scalability
# There is already a LVM pool called Storage
# Use lsblk or fdisk -l to identify the drives and keep them in your head eg:sdb,sdc,sdd and so on
# replace /dev/sdX, new_volume_group, new_logical_volume, existing_volume_group, and existing_logical_volume with your actual disk, volume group, and logical volume names. 
# Adjust sizes and names as per your requirements,this creates a logic volume of all the space

Creating a New Logical Volume:
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Add New Disk in Proxmox GUI:
# Format the disk, so backup anything imp 

# 2. Create LVM Physical Volume (PV):
pvcreate /dev/sdX

# 3. Create a New Volume Group (VG):
vgcreate new_volume_group /dev/sdX

# 4. Create a New Logical Volume (LV):
lvcreate -L 50G -n new_logical_volume new_volume_group

# 5. Create a Filesystem:
mkfs.ext4 /dev/new_volume_group/new_logical_volume

# 6. Mount the Filesystem:
mkdir /mnt/new_logical_volume
mount /dev/new_volume_group/new_logical_volume /mnt/new_logical_volume

# 7. Verify Changes:
lvdisplay
df -h

Resizing an Existing Logical Volume:
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Add New Disk in Proxmox GUI:
# Format the disk, so backup anything imp 

# 2. Create LVM Physical Volume (PV):
pvcreate /dev/sdX

# 3. Extend Existing Volume Group (VG):
vgextend existing_volume_group /dev/sdX

# 4. Resize Logical Volumes (LVs):
lvextend -l +100%FREE /dev/existing_volume_group/existing_logical_volume

# 5. Resize the Filesystem:
resize2fs /dev/existing_volume_group/existing_logical_volume

# 6. Verify Changes:
lvdisplay
df -h


